title: For Sale/Trade:  Walther PPS 9mm w/ extras - 6 mags - holsters
postcontent:
The Walther PPS is the ultimate CCW pistol. A very elegant pistol, legendary Walther quality, plenty of firepower and under an inch thick. Compared to normal double stack or even sub-compact pistols, this thing conceals like no other. When it's inside the waistband you could forget that you even have it on you.

This listing includes over $350 in extras (4 extra mags = $200+, 3 holsters = $150+)

This is for a Walther PPS with many extras. From the factory, this pistol comes with two magazines, I'm throwing in four (4) extras for a total of six (6) mags. Two 8 rounders, three 7 rounders, one 6 rounder (flush). I personally like and typically carried with the 7 round magazine. The 8 rounders and 6 rounder have each been loaded maybe once at the range. Note that these magazines are hard to find and when you can find them in stock they are usually over $50. So that is $200 in those extra 4 magazines.

I am the original owner of this PPS and have owned it for about 3 years. It has been one of my primary pistols for CCW, but I only have about 400 - 500 rounds through it. It eats all of the ammo I've thrown at it, from 115 grain range ammo to 147 grain Federal HST, and I've never had a failure of any sort, even in the break in period - a super reliable, accurate, low recoil little shooter.

I'm also including three (3) holsters. They are all IWB holsters and custom formed to this gun - a leather, combo leather/kydex, and a kydex holster with (removable) mag holster attached. The cost of these three holsters was about $165 total.

Comes with the pistol, 6 mags, 3 holsters, original Walther PPS case, and manual.

Compare to Springfield XDs, Smith & Wesson M&P Shield, Kahr PM9 or other super slim single stack pistols.

Must be CO resident and legally able to purchase and own a pistol in the state of Colorado. Must show ID (CCW preferred) and willing to sign a bill of sale.

title: For Sale:  Custom/aftermarket JRC (Just Right Carbine) .45 ACP
postcontent:
Just Right Carbine .45 ACP.  If you go to youtube and find the extremely thorough review of the JRC rifle by a Mr. Jared Price this rifle comes from the factory with quite a few engineering oversights.  I have done all the modifications that Mr. price recommends for this weapon except for adding a long sear and a full length bolt guide rail which were out of my abilities and capabilities at this time.  All gun smithing modifications were precision machined by hand on a bench top lathe and mill. 

Custom Mods:

Getting rid of the screws that JRC uses/used to attach the lower receiver to the upper receiver and replacing them with precision machined extended take down pins, springs, detents - the whole 9 yards.  Just this mod makes tear down for cleaning and maintenance 10X easier and more user friendly than the stock set up.  This modification required machining of the lower pistol grip, exposing the raw aluminum.  Nobody would want to buy a gun with exposed areas of aluminum so I chemically stripped the very cheap/poor factory black anodizing off of the lower pistol grip, lower mag well, upper receiver, buffer tube,  and free float quad rail hand guard (I did all the parts to maintain uniformity) and had them all professionally re-surfaced with type 3 hard coat anodize, leaving these aluminum parts with an incredibly hard, essentially scratch proof protective surface with a dark graphite grey matte finish.  From the pics you can see the finished product looks awesome, with the tan butt stock, grey body, and black accessories.  

3/32 removed from the cartridge ejection pin for increased live round ejection clearance in the event if a misfire, which stock from the factory this weapon tends to do because of its short firing pin.  The weapon can now cycle live ammo as it should with no problems.  

Speaking of short firing pin, I turned a brand new adjustable length firing pin out of heat treated steel on my lathe.  It is currently set to 3/16" longer-than-stock.  Longer firing pin allows for consistent full primer strikes during rapid fire or any firing rate for that matter.  From the factory this thing had a problem with rapid fire misfires because of light primer strikes/no primer strikes due to a short firing pin, which in turn caused the weapon to need to eject live rounds which before the mods was a problem due to the already mentioned issue with the cartridge ejection pin.  I also bought a factory replacement firing pin from directly from JRC which will obviously be include with the gun.

I drilled and tapped the buffer tube and buffer tube adapter for 1/4-20 socket cap set screws (seen in one of the pictures).  This solved one of the biggest hassles with the gun, which was dis-assembly for cleaning and maintenance.  This setup allows for quick and easy removal/re-securing of the buffer tube which is required whenever you want to remove the bolt.  This setup means that a spanner wrench is no longer mandatory to screw/unscrew the factory castle nut that originally secured the buffer tube to the upper.  All you need now is a small 1/8 hex wrench to work the set screw and the castle nut can simply be hand tightened.  The hex wrench fits easily in the butt stock storage compartment so that it is with you whenever you need it.

With the addition of the pins mod and buffer tube set screw mod this weapon can be taken down in less than twenty seconds, which is exponentially faster and simpler than the way you had to tear down the stock weapon.

I know all this stuff will pry scare people off but: One, I want potential buyers to know exactly what they are getting.  I'm not trying to scam anybody, because the salesman/store I bought this thing from failed to mention any of the very obvious flaws with the stock gun.  Granted I pry should have done some research but, I mean come on.  Two, I've got this gun rockin' and rollin' now.  It looks sweet, and it fires phenomenally.  Weapon is quite accurate, at least for me, but that is a subjective statement, as it really depends on the shooter.  It has extremely, EXTREMELY low recoil (a baby could shoot it).  Three, even though the factory design and engineering were suspect with regards to a few features, the materials this weapon is made of are top notch.  Anything having to do with the bolt is a very hard/tough steel alloy of some sort...I found that out the hard way when trying to machine the firing pin.    Excellent factory barrel.  The factory machining is exquisite and the factory finish is flawless.  I could not duplicate it with my home machines, but I feel my machining is very good and blends nicely with the factory finish.  

Aftermarket Parts/Accessories:

-MAGPUL ACS-L extendable butt stock w/ storage compartment (desert tan).  
-Factory butt stock 
-MAGPUL AFG2 angled fore grip w/ optional finger shelf (black).  
-Cheap vertical fore grip (black)
-ErgoGrip rubberized pistol grip (black)
-TRU-BRITE multi-reticle/dual color open red-dot series optic (red and green colors, 4 different reticle options, and 5 brightness settings)(black).  
-MAGPUL front and rear flip-up polymer "iron sights" (black).  
-Soft rubber low profile hand guard covers (black).
-JRC factory combination wrench for easy dis-assembly of the butt stock, fore end, and barrel.  
-Two (2) 13 round Glock 45 magazines.
-One (1) high cap. 27 round Glock 45 magazine (haven't got through a full mag yet without having a loading issue with this mag) 
-Movable front sling attachment bracket.  
-Padded black rifle carrying case with 4 external Velcro closure mag pouches/storage   pouches and one long zippered storage pouch.  
-Rifle cleaning kit.  
-Rifle lock and key.
-Spare take down pin detent pins, springs, (from Brownells) and 6-32 retaining set screws
-Spare (first attempt) custom take down pins (which will work in a pinch if something happens to the good ones)
-Spare 1/4-20 buffer tube set screws.
-Safety glasses
-High speed shooting gloves.
~100 - 400 rounds  (45 ACP:  winchester, remington, blazer, american eagle, speer gold dot HP +P)
-All misc. hex keys that are required for tear down and adjustments
-Instructions/manuals

Standard Features:

 Straight blow back operated, pistol caliber carbine rifle with a modular design for converting between .45 ACP, .40 SW, and 9mm (.40 SW and 9mm kits sold separately).  16.25" barrel.  Designed to accept standard Glock magazines allowing for rapid pistol to rifle changeover (provided you have a Glock).  Free float barrel surrounded by a 4 railed handguard (Picatinny) with Picatinny rail integrated along the length of the upper receiver (aka. plenty of room for attachments).  Ambidextrous (L or R) ejection and charging handle accommodates left and right handed shooters.  Factory threaded barrel for suppressors, compensators, or muzzle brakes, and/or things of that nature.  M4/AR furniture and trigger fittings allows for compatibility with the thousands and thousands of M4/AR aftermarket parts you can find online or at your local dealer.  Made NY, USA!

Weapon has had maybe 500 rounds through it.  Bought it for home defense hastily the day after I though I heard someone/thing in the house (turned out to be my imagination) and after I did post purchase research I realized I had my work cut out for me.  It went from being a weapon for defense/protection to a project gun almost over night.  All the mods took about 3 months to complete, they weren't turned out in a rush over night.  
Unfortunately for me I bought this thing on a whim with no regard for the horrible timing it was for me to buy a weapon as I am moving to a small apartment in Florida later this summer to attend medical school...so in about a month I see it collecting dust up in the closet somewhere.  Also throughout the build I became more interested in the machining than in the gun.   I want it to go to a good home and for somebody to benefit from my hasty purchase.  New in box with minimal to no accessories this weapon is sold for roughly $700-$800.  Take advantage of this package.   Have many more pics, just ask.  Price is negotiable (its more of a starting point).  Questions please email Matt at - REDACTED, or call or text Matt at three three zero-7 0 1-six six 9 2.  I will also split shipping.

The new Beretta Px4 Storm pistol is the most advanced expression of technological and aesthetic features in a semiautomatic sidearm. Built around a modular concept that a pistol can be adapted to different needs and modes of operations, without compromising on ergonomics and the renowned Beretta reliability and performance, the Px4 Storm emphasizes power, ease of handling, performance and reliability.
Manufactured in three calibers, the Px4 Storm uses an exclusive Beretta designed innovative locked-breech with a rotating barrel system, the strongest action to date. 
The light yet durable frame employs modern thermoplastic technology through the use of technopolymer reinforced fiberglass. Modular structure, ergonomics and interchangeability of parts make the Px4 Storm the ideal firearm for law-enforcement use, as well as personal defense.
1. Accessory Rail: The frame of the Px4 Storm has an integral Picatinny MILSTD-1913 rail for rapid attachment of tactical lights and laser aiming devices.
2. Slide: The sides of the slide are smooth and offer snag-proof insertion and removal of the pistol from its holster. The front and rear serrations on the slide facilitate slide operation and safety control in both wet or dry conditions.

Other PX4 Accessories 3. Visible Automatic Firing Pin Block: The front part of the firing pin is blocked from any forward movement until the trigger is pulled completely back. The block is
located rearward, far away from the fouling and debris of the breech face. Since the block is visible, the user may ascertain its proper operation at any time. Even if the pistol falls and strikes the ground muzzle down, the firing pin will not strike the primer.
4. 3-Dot Sight System: Features a white ‘3-dot’ sight pattern for quick acquisition of the target. The rear sight is designed to provide a front projection so that, in
an emergency, the user may retract the slide single-handedly by pushing the rear sight against the edge of a table, door, etc.
5. Ambidextrous Safety (Type F): The ambidextrous safety lever, easily accessible by the thumb or a right or left handed shooter, is spring loaded so it’s either positively “on” or “off”. The safety lever also functions as the pistol’s decocking lever. When pushed down, the rear part of the firing pin (striker) is rotated out of alignment with the front part of the firing pin. (NOTE: Type C does not have an external safety/decocking lever). Additional hammer drop catch (half cock notch) prevents striking of the firing pin unit in the remote chance of unintentional hammer drop.
6. External Hammer Design: A traditional feature of Beretta pistols, this design provides the most energy to the firing pin, virtually eliminating the possibility of
misfires due to light primer strikes. Also provides an immediate visual and tactile indicator as to the cocked/uncocked status of the pistol.
7. Individual Size Grips: Pistol may be configured with small, medium or large backstraps to individually fit the hand of each shooter. The backstraps are checkered to ensure a firm grip in both wet or dry shooting conditions. Three backstraps included with every pistol.
8. Reversible Magazine Release: Multiple-sized, reversible magazine release buttons allow for customization to the individual’s hand size. Small size comes standard on the gun, while medium and large buttons are available as accessories and easy replacement. Each size may be positioned for right-handed or left-handed use. 

9. Simple Field Stripping: Pistol is designed for extremely quick and simple field stripping. Disassembly latch does not remove from the gun, preventing accidental
dropping and loss. Reassembly is easy and accidental misassembly of parts is prevented by the distinctive design.
10. Light Technopolymer Frame: The light, yet durable, frame employs modern thermoplastic technology through the use of Corrosion resistant fiberglass reinforced polymer.
11. Barrrel: The Px4’s unique rotating barrel and locking system dissipates recoil energy radially, reducing felt recoil and muzzle rise. This is the strongest Beretta pistol action. Chrome lined barrels provide extreme corrosion resistance, as well as ease of cleaning. Barrels also feature a deeply recessed combat muzzle crown to protect the rifling.

Up for Auction is an Extremely Rare Pre-WWII Springfield M1 Garand Rifle originally made between 1936 and 1937 with the Gas Trap gas system. This rifle was converted to the Gas Port configuration as most were. This is a low 4 digit serial number rifle. After WWII started this rifle and many others were re-barreled with new barrels and issued to GI's who fought in Europe, as the prior owner of this rifle did. The America Hero who was issued this rifle and fought and landed on the beaches of Normandy recently has passed away making this Piece of American History available.
